Nollywood quartet, Chioma Akpotha, Ufuoma McDermott, Uche Jombo and Omoni Oboli, popularly known as Dubai Girls, have kicked off the 2022 Travel Raffle Competition, for those interested in traveling to the United Arab Emirates. Winners of the 2022 Dubai Girls Travel Raffle competition, whych is being sponsored by the Dubai’s Department of Economy and Tourism (DET) will join the Nollywood stars, on the trip that will take place from September 5 through 12, 2022. A statement made available to LEADERSHIP in Port Harcourt, stated that benefits and attractions include of the five-day trip, include free accommodation for two, meals, access to the activities of the Dubai girls and lots of surprises. Speaking about the trip, McDermott said the four Nollywood actresses had been on the trip twice, in 2018 and 2019, describing Dubai as an inspiration. McDermott said: “Dubai is no longer a city to me. It’s an inspiration. Each visit resets my goals and rejuvenates my God given abilities. This visit has me pondering on a new excitement based on new discoveries, new adventures and new infrastructure.” Also speaking, another actress, Oboli said: “The Dubai girls trip this year will be fun and bonding pro max. You already know the Dubai girls are bringing the heat so come fully prepared to have the fun of your life. My bags are already packed.” On her part, Jombo said she looks forward to moments and memories they girls create whenever they visit the UAE city. Jombo said: “Dubai is one of the most beautiful cities to visit for me and I bond with my girls all over again anytime we visit. I love the city, the experience, the places I visit and always look forward to the moments/memories we create.” Also speaking, Akpotha said: “Dubai the beautiful city of gold with modern features and luxury at its peak! The safest city I have ever been to, never had to worry about anything. When Dubai calls, I just pick my passport and go…no need to pack a bag.”